    "Moreover, in consideration of the current focus of alignment research and the probable locus of foreseeable catastrophic risk, I will limit myself to machine learning proposals.Following Hubinger [38], we can distinguish alignment proposals according to their training goal and their training rationale.",
    "The training goal comprises the general sort of algorithm the model is intended to learn, and why learning that sort of algorithm is good.The training rationale explains why the training setup will lead the model to learn the training goal.",
    "Hubinger enumerates seven different training goals: 1.",
    "Loss-minimizing agents: a model which has an internal representation of the training loss and explicitly aims to minimize it. 2.",
    "Fully aligned agents: a model which shares the goals of humans, and optimizes for themfoot_5 3."
